{"id": 231226350, "title": "Two cars destroyed in Glasgow as fire rips through peaceful southside neighbourhood", "text": "A southside woman has been left shocked after a fire ripped through a 'peaceful' southside neighbourhood in the early hours of the morning. Lorn MacDonald had just left her home in the Gorbals at around 4am on Saturday, June 8, when she noticed black smoke billowing into the air from McNeil Street. The hospitality worker turned the corner to find the street glowing orange with flames coming from two cars. The local phoned 999 but moments later fire crews arrived after being called by someone else. Police are now investigating the fire which left two cars burnt out wrecks and left a third damaged. READ MORE: Man dies on Glasgow west end street as forensic teams scour scene following 'unexplained' incident READ MORE:Glasgow M8 food delivery e-bike 'seized' after trying to enter busy motorway Speaking to Glasgow Live, she said: \"I came outside and noticed some black smoke rising behind an opposite building. I immediately contacted 999. \"Not knowing exactly where it was from. But it looked bad. \"As I took a walk while on the phone to the emergency service to give them more information I watched the fire engine drive up the street. Someone had already just called them. And they tackled it fairly quickly. \"It was quite ablaze before they got there. It was hard to tell how many cars were actually alight. I then left them to it and went back to bed. I got a shock. It\u2019s such a peaceful neighbourhood. I hope this wasn\u2019t deliberate. A Police Scotland spokesperson said: \"Around 4.10am on Saturday, 8 June, 2024, we attended McNeil Street, Glasgow where three vehicles were on fire. \"The fire was extinguished by Scottish Fire and Rescue Service and enquiries will be carried out to establish the cause.\" A spokesperson for the Scottish Fire and Rescue Service said: \"The call came in at 4.02am at McNeil Street in Glasgow. \"We had reports of two cars on fire and we did attend. The fire was extinguished and the area secured.\" Join Glasgow Live's WhatsApp community here and get the latest news sent straight to your messages. Sign up to our daily Glasgow Live newsletter here to receive news and features direct to your inbox", "summary": "Lorn MacDonald had just left her home in the Gorbals at around 4am on Saturday, June 8, when she noticed black smoke billowing into the air from McNeil Street.", "url": "https://www.glasgowlive.co.uk/news/glasgow-news/two-cars-destroyed-glasgow-fire-29317615", "image": "https://i2-prod.glasgowlive.co.uk/incoming/article29317669.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/0_Screenshot-2277.png", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-08 12:25:59", "author": "Jordan Shepherd", "authors": ["Jordan Shepherd"], "language": "en", "catgory": "entertainment", "source_country": "GB", "sentiment": -0.738}